+## Event-Aware Generation
+
+When the user wants ideas for a daily playground, portfolio sprint, launch window, or social/shareable experiment, include a timely-source pass before generating ideas:
+
+- Identify nearby events: holidays, festivals, conferences, product launches, tool events, sports/cultural moments, seasons, anniversaries, or platform-specific rituals.
+- Use events as constraints, not themes pasted on top. Translate the event into behavior, material, data, timing, ritual, or audience context.
+- Prefer adjacent interpretations over obvious decoration. A Fourth of July idea might explore burst physics, civic archives, heat, night photography, neighborhood sound, or synchronized countdowns rather than just flags and fireworks.
+- For platform events such as Figma Config, connect the idea to the community's real workflows: plugins, component systems, design tokens, collaboration, prototype handoff, critique, or conference-session artifacts.
+- Keep it buildable in the user's time box and useful after the event when possible.
+
+If event timing matters and current-date knowledge may be stale, verify dates before relying on them.
